> I am not sure the first patch is correct.
> 
> `MakePrivate` doesn't create a new bind mount if the target is already a mountpoint (it uses `github.com/moby/sys/mountinfo/mountinfo.go`)

one thing to investigate to just reuse the home mount point when it exists for any reason is to attempt directly `mount(MS_PRIVATE, target)` and only do the bind mount if it fails with `EINVAL`, so we also avoid the potential slow check for the mount point.  @kolyshkin what do you think?

```go
func ensureMountedAs(mnt string, flags int) error {
        mounted, err := Mounted(mnt)
        if err != nil {
                return err
        }

        if !mounted {
                if err := mount(mnt, mnt, "none", uintptr(BIND), ""); err != nil {
                        return err
                }
        }

        return mount("", mnt, "none", uintptr(flags), "")
}
```

should become something like (completely untested): 

```go
func ensureMountedAs(mnt string, flags int) error {
        err := mount("", mnt, "none", uintptr(flags), "") 
        if err == nil {
            return nil
        }

         if !errors.Is(err, syscall.EINVAL) {
             return err
         }

        // mnt is not a mountpoint, create a bind mount on itself
        if err := mount(mnt, mnt, "none", uintptr(BIND), ""); err != nil {
            return err
        }

        return mount("", mnt, "none", uintptr(flags), "")
}
```
